#: ../../../filesystems/smb/smbdirect.rst:5
msgid "SMB Direct - SMB3 over RDMA"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/smb/smbdirect.rst:7
msgid ""
"This document describes how to set up the Linux SMB client and server to use "
"RDMA."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/smb/smbdirect.rst:11
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/smb/smbdirect.rst:12
msgid ""
"The Linux SMB kernel client supports SMB Direct, which is a transport scheme "
"for SMB3 that uses RDMA (Remote Direct Memory Access) to provide high "
"throughput and low latencies by bypassing the traditional TCP/IP stack. SMB "
"Direct on the Linux SMB client can be tested against KSMBD - a kernel-space "
"SMB server."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/smb/smbdirect.rst:20
msgid "Installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/smb/smbdirect.rst:21
msgid ""
"Install an RDMA device. As long as the RDMA device driver is supported by "
"the kernel, it should work. This includes both software emulators (soft "
"RoCE, soft iWARP) and hardware devices (InfiniBand, RoCE, iWARP)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/smb/smbdirect.rst:25
msgid ""
"Install a kernel with SMB Direct support. The first kernel release to "
"support SMB Direct on both the client and server side is 5.15. Therefore, a "
"distribution compatible with kernel 5.15 or later is required."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/smb/smbdirect.rst:29
msgid ""
"Install cifs-utils, which provides the `mount.cifs` command to mount SMB "
"shares."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/smb/smbdirect.rst:32
msgid "Configure the RDMA stack"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/smb/smbdirect.rst:34
msgid ""
"Make sure that your kernel configuration has RDMA support enabled. Under "
"Device Drivers -> Infiniband support, update the kernel configuration to "
"enable Infiniband support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/smb/smbdirect.rst:38
msgid ""
"Enable the appropriate IB HCA support or iWARP adapter support, depending on "
"your hardware."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/smb/smbdirect.rst:41
msgid "If you are using InfiniBand, enable IP-over-InfiniBand support."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../filesystems/smb/smbdirect.rst:43
msgid ""
"For soft RDMA, enable either the soft iWARP (`RDMA _SIW`) or soft RoCE "
"(`RDMA_RXE`) module. Install the `iproute2` package and use the `rdma link "
"add` command to load the module and create an RDMA interface."
msgstr ""

